Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Cocaine Girls in the West End - Orgasm
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00ft5kk
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 15 Dec 2008
Laurie Taylor explores the latest research into how society works. Was the Imperial era the result of repressed sexuality? A new book claims that forbidden desires lie behind the West's great cultural output. Laurie talks to Robert Muchembled, author of Orgasm and the West, and historian Joanna Bourke. Show less